tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE FingerprintScanData (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  fingerprint_data BYTEA,
  scan_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  user_id INT,
  location_id INT
)

CREATE TABLE scan_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    scan_id INT,
    analysis_result VARCHAR(50),
    analysis_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (scan_id) REFERENCES fingerprint_scans(id)
);

CREATE TABLE fingerprint_scans (
   id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   fingerprint_data BYTEA NOT NULL,
   scan_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE users (
   user_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
   last_login TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE anomaly_patterns (
   pattern_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   pattern_description TEXT NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE anomalies_detected (
   anomaly_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   scan_id INT REFERENCES fingerprint_scans(id),
   pattern_id INT REFERENCES anomaly_patterns(pattern_id),
   detection_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
)
